HEADWORD: Tallyman
<hw>Tal"ly*man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Tallymen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who keeps
the tally, or marks the sticks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who keeps a tally shop, or conducts his business
as tally trade.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Talma</ent>⟦br⟧
